            "title": "Los Angeles to Sell $86 Million in Bonds to Address Homelessness",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Josh Beckerman </p><br/><p>\n  The City of Los Angeles plans to sell $86 million of general obligation bonds, with proceeds slated for housing and services for people experiencing or at risk of homelessness. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The taxable series 2026-A social bonds are being issued pursuant to Proposition HHH, approved in 2016. The bonds will use the remaining principal of the $1.2 billion authorization, according to a sale notice on MuniOS. </p><p>\n\n  The city plans to use proceeds and other funding for 39 projects expected to provide 2,394 permanent supportive housing units. </p><p>\n\n  A competitive sale is expected Jan. 15 at 9 a.m. PST, with closing expected Jan. 27 according to a roadshow document. </p><p>\n\n  Maturity is expected to range from 2027 through 2045. Bidders may provide that all of the securities are serial bonds or that certain amounts may be combined into term bonds. </p><p>\n\n  Bonds maturing on or after Sept. 1, 2036, are subject to optional redemption on and after Sept. 1, 2035. </p><p>\n\n  Fitch Ratings has assigned an AAA rating to the bonds. The rating firm, which has an AA+ rating for the city, said Dec. 23 that its outlook for the city's rating remained negative, citing factors including a structural budgetary imbalance and wildfire-related expense and revenue loss. </p><p>\n\n  Moody's rated the bonds Aa2. </p><p>\n\n  In 2025, City of Los Angeles transactions included a $1.51 billion sale of tax and revenue anticipation notes in June. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Josh Beckerman at josh.beckerman@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  01-14-26 1540ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/los-angeles-to-sell-86-million-in-bonds-to-address-homelessness-ce7e58d9d88ff026",
